item.title: Need help with a server error
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Are you running uTorrent by chance?

If so, set the port in uTorrent to anything other than 43594.

Then run your server. After it launches, change the port back to 43594 in uTorrent.

item.title: Need help with a server error
item.dc:creator: @runescape_sucks runescape sucks
item.description:
@runescape_sucks wrote:

This just means that either you have another instance of the server running, or you have a program that is bound to the same port your server is running on.
